verbose_text: OH can be produced from gamma-rays of 60 Co and by Fenton reactions of Fe (II) or Cu (II) ions with hydrogen peroxide.31,32 H 2 O 2 exists in human cells, Fe (II) ions are physiologically necessary for iron containing proteins, and Cu (II) ions exist in blood plasma and cell nuclei.
evidence: Fe(II) ions are physiologically necessary for iron
